==English==

===Etymology===
First attested around 1425. From {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|absorber}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|assorbir}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|absorbeō||swallow up}}, from {{m|la|ab||from}} + {{m|la|sorbeō||suck in, swallow}}. Compare French {{m|fr|absorber}}.

